headline: From Monroe to Trump: Two centuries of US interference in Latin America
subhead: From the Monroe Doctrine of 1823 to the intervention in Venezuela, Washington has dominated the American continent by force and through economic power. Faced with China's growing influence, Donald Trump has rejuvenated the notion of a 'manifest destiny.'

headline: Trump threatens Europe with tariffs over Greenland as protesters rally
Denmark's Greenlandic community worries: 'Our very existence is at stake'
EU and Mercosur sign 'historic' free trade deal
subhead: Saturday's signing ceremony in Paraguay's capital of Asunción marks a major geopolitical victory for the EU in an age of American tariffs and surging Chinese exports. 'The geopolitical importance of this agreement cannot be overstated,' said Commission President Ursula von der Leyen.

headline: By appearing with a royal heiress, Jordan Bardella risks blurring his image
subhead: The president of the far-right Rassemblement National presents himself as the 'authentic spokesperson for a France despised by the elites,' yet was photographed in the company of the daughter of Prince Carlo of Bourbon-Two Sicilies, Duke of Castro.

headline: French Response, the foreign service's account for trolling disinformation targeting France
subhead: Since 2025, the unconventional X account French Response has delivered sharp English-language retorts and headline-grabbing moments on the social network. Experts call it an effective way to counter attempts at foreign interference, though it raises questions about its long-term usefulness.

headline: Henrique Gouveia e Melo, the admiral who wants to lead Portugal
subhead: Revealed during the Covid-19 pandemic, former military officer Henrique Gouveia e Melo is in the race for the January 18 presidential election. He has attracted voters with his talk of reform, despite his limited grasp of political conventions.

'That 'Stranger Things' brings Prince or David Bowie back to life is both wonderful and dreadful'
subhead: In the final episode of the hit Netflix series, 15- to 25-year-olds discovered 'Purple Rain' and 'Heroes,' whose streams have soared across music platforms. Unfortunately, the younger generation has limited itself to these snippets, showing little interest in the artists or their discographies, writes Michel Guerrin, editor-in-chief of Le Monde, in his column.

headline: Yann Le Cun: 'Why I'm leaving Meta to launch my own AI start-up'
subhead: The former head of artificial intelligence research at Meta explains his decision to start a new company focused on the physical world, citing strategic differences with the American tech giant and predicting a 'third AI revolution' in the coming years.

headline: Venezuela two weeks after Maduro's abduction: 'I was scared, then I cried with joy. Now, I'm scared again'
subhead: Following the abduction of Nicolas Maduro, who has led Venezuela since 2013, Le Monde collected accounts from residents of Caracas and its suburbs.
